-- NKT's core profit below forecast in Q1, keeps 2014 outlook
-- 
-- Wed May 14, 2014 02:28AM EDT
-- None



COPENHAGEN, May 14 (Reuters) - Danish industrial group NKT Holding <NKT.CO> reported first-quarter core profit (EBITDA) below forecast on Wednesday and kept its 2014 guidance unchanged.

Earnings before interest, tax, depreciation and amortisation rose to 254 million Danish crowns ($46.64 million) from 217 million in the same quarter last year, while the average forecast in a Reuters poll had predicted a result of 280 million. The company, which makes cleaning machines and power cables, kept its full-year 2014 guidance for an operational EBITDA margin between 9 percent and 9.5 percent, and organic sales growth of between 0 and 3 percent.